HEADWORD: Aonian
<hw>A*o"ni*an</hw> <pr>(⟦asl⟧*⟦omac⟧"n⟦icr⟧*<i>a</i>n)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From <ets>Aonia</ets>, a part of B⟦oe⟧otia, in
Greece.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to Aonia, in B⟦oe⟧otia, or to the Muses,
who were supposed to dwell there.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Aonian fount</b></col>, <cd>the fountain of Aganippe, at
the foot of Mount Helicon, not far from Thebes, and sacred to the
Muses.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aorist</ent>⟦br⟧
